Testes 26–34 (29, n = 14) in number; in 2 or 3 layers, in one continuous posterior field, sometimes overlapping osmoregulatory canals and often overlapping posterior lobes of ovary and vitellarium (
Fig. 2
). External vas deferens convoluted in antero-poral part of median field. Cirrus-sac elongate, 170–212 × 36–50 (191 × 43, n = 20), usually straight, crossing osmoregulatory canals; distal extremity with large cells (
Fig. 3
). Internal vas deferens forming several coils, mostly in proximal half of cirrus sac. Cirrus unarmed, about 100–130 long and usually straight when invaginated.
